1)Add a User in a kali linux
Command :- adduser username
2)Network Setting In Kali Linux
IP Address
Command :- sudo ifconfig -a
3)IP address and Netmask Network Configuration
Command:- sudo ifconfig eth0 127.0.0.1 netmask 255.0.0.0
Configure Services In Kali Linux
Command :- service ssh start
Command :- ssh username@hostname
4)Basic Command To Run , Enable , Start and Stop Services
Command :- systemctl [command] [service_name]
5)To stop and restart the service in Linux, use the command:
Command :- sudo systemctl restart SERVICE_NAME
Command :- sudo systemctl stop SERVICE_NAME
6)To Enable Services At Boot
Command :- sudo systemctl enable SERVICE_NAME
7)To display the list of services which are running In Kali Linux
Command :- sudo systemctl -t=service --state=running
Sudo settings
8)Command :- sudo apt install -y software_name
Any Command Which Are Used With Sudo Give A User A Super User Advantage.
